OL,8,Flegal advice on the Government deal.
OL,10,FMr Bryson was asked about the
OL,11,Fpossibility of loyalist and unionist
OL,12,Fprotests in opposition to the return
OL,13,Fof Stormont.
OL,15,F"It may well be the case that people
OL,16,Ftake the opportunity to do that, and
OL,17,Fif they do, they should do it
OL,18,Fpeacefully and lawfully, there's a
OL,19,Fsignificant strength of feeling," he
OL,20,Fsaid.
